                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/553.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of the 14th instant. Explain to the Government that Janes has
                    already been appointed arbitrator and that it is now too late to defer his
                    departure. Transmit to Janes at Panama a duplicate of the note of the Foreign
                    Office. Such instructions as may be necessary will be sent upon the receipt of
                    the note here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
